content:
Git can be configured more than just name and email.
Git configurations are located in &ldquo;global&rdquo; as well as in local &ldquo;repository&rdquo;
# List config in global by using flag &quot;global&quot; $ git config --global --list # List config in local repository. It also inherits from global config $ git config --list # Update name and email $ git config --global user.name &quot;Abracus Doe&quot; $ git config --global user.email &quot;abracus.doe@example.org&quot; # Update the default editor $ git config core.editor &quot;vim&quot; $ git config core.editor &quot;nvim&quot; # Add color to ui $ git config color.ui false Reference Customizing git
